# i18n Conventions

## Message Files

- `src/messages/pt.json` (default locale), `src/messages/en.json`
- Nested structure: `pages.*` for page content, `components.*` for shared UI, `metadata.*` for SEO

## Usage Patterns

```jsx
// Simple translations (with namespace)
const t = useTranslations("pages");
t("about.title")

// Array data (practice areas, articles, nav links)
const { getTranslationsArray } = useTranslation();
const items = getTranslationsArray("components.practiceAreas");
```

## Rules

- Every page must export `getStaticProps` that loads messages for the locale
- The `Button` component translates its `label` prop internally via `components.buttons` namespace — pass plain string keys, not pre-translated values
- Server-side config lives in `src/i18n/request.js` (used by `next-intl/plugin`)
- When adding new text, add keys to BOTH `en.json` and `pt.json`
